WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.130 --> 00:00:02.810
By intrusion, we mean any attack

00:00:02.810 --> 00:00:07.640
that aims to compromise the security
ghost of an organization.

00:00:07.640 --> 00:00:13.180
For example, performing a remote
root compromise, of an email server.

00:00:13.180 --> 00:00:17.140
Defacing a web server to
display inappropriate content.

00:00:17.140 --> 00:00:20.100
Guessing and cracking stolen passwords.

00:00:20.100 --> 00:00:23.540
Stealing a database containing
credit card numbers.

00:00:23.540 --> 00:00:26.750
Reading sensitive data
without authorization.

00:00:26.750 --> 00:00:30.350
Running a packet sniffer on
a workstation, to capture user names and

00:00:30.350 --> 00:00:32.390
passwords on a network.

00:00:32.390 --> 00:00:36.130
Using a permission error
on an anonymous FTP server,

00:00:36.130 --> 00:00:39.680
to distribute pirated software and
music files.

00:00:39.680 --> 00:00:45.270
Dialing into an unsecured modem, and
gaining internal network access.

00:00:45.270 --> 00:00:49.270
Posing as a company executive,
calling the help desk and

00:00:49.270 --> 00:00:52.110
resetting the executives email account.

00:00:52.110 --> 00:00:54.000
Using a workstation without permission.

